OL,7,FHe was found unconscious 6 hours later
OL,8,Fby his family, at around 5pm on 30
OL,9,FNovember, and taken to hospital, but
OL,10,Fthe bleeding on his brain was
OL,11,Finoperable and he died two days later
OL,12,Fon 2 December.
OL,14,FThe coroner said she could not
OL,15,Freconcile the evidence from Ms
OL,16,FChatterton which was that she messaged
OL,17,Fher line manager to say Mr Ginger had
OL,18,Fcollapsed - but that she meant
OL,19,Fcollapsed "emotionally".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
